This module will be extended, or modified as required. Videoframe Systems reserves the right to make changes in specification and other information contained in this document without prior notice. vfProductsSignalMonitoringFrameReg.name: vfProductsSignalMonitoringFrameReg
vfProductsSignalMonitoringFrameReg.description: Videoframe signal monitoring frame with hot-swappable modules, and monitoring via SNMP and gvg modular protocol.

vfProductsVF200Reg.name: vfProductsVF200Reg
vfProductsVF200Reg.description: VF200 2RU modular frame for Signal Monitoring and machine control functions.

vfFrameSlotTable.name: vfFrameSlotTable
vfFrameSlotTable.description: Each row contains information about one slot in the managed VF200 frame.

vfFrameSlotEntry.name: vfFrameSlotEntry
vfFrameSlotEntry.description: Information about one slot in the managed VF200 frame.

vfFrameSlotStatus.name: vfFrameSlotStatus
vfFrameSlotStatus.description: State of this slot. Illegal means the slot does not exist. moduleValid means the correct firmware has been loaded to the module and it is ready for operation.

vfModuleTypeRegObjectID.name: vfModuleTypeRegObjectID
vfModuleTypeRegObjectID.description: MIB-registered identification of the module currently installed in this slot.

vfModuleTypeRootOID.name: vfModuleTypeRootOID
vfModuleTypeRootOID.description: Root OID of the module-specific managed information for the module currently installed in this slot.

vfModulePartNo.name: vfModulePartNo
vfModulePartNo.description: Videoframe part no. of module currently installed in slot - should match module nameplate.

vfModuleDescription.name: vfModuleDescription
vfModuleDescription.description: Description of module currently installed in slot - should match module nameplate.

vfModuleTrapEnable.name: vfModuleTrapEnable
vfModuleTrapEnable.description: Enables or disables the Trap that is associated with a slot status change event or module event.

vfModuleAlarmAutoReArm.name: vfModuleAlarmAutoReArm
vfModuleAlarmAutoReArm.description: Enables or disables automatic re-arming of alarms from signal monitoring modules.

vfFrameOfflineSwitch.name: vfFrameOfflineSwitch
vfFrameOfflineSwitch.description: Indicates the state of the 'offline' switch for the frame. 'offline' indicates the switch is set to take the frame offline.

vfFrameLocateIndicator.name: vfFrameLocateIndicator
vfFrameLocateIndicator.description: Set to flash (1) to cause the locate LED on the front of the frame to begin flashing. Set to off to stop flashing. This is used to verify the identity of a particular unit among racks of units.

vfFrameAdminState.name: vfFrameAdminState
vfFrameAdminState.description: The desired operational state of this device. Use this object to command the frame to a different operational state (vfBoxState from the vf-generic MIB module). NOTE: It is mandatory that a managed device support all of the enumerated device states. vfFrameOnline(1) - The device is running and ready to process load. vfFrameInMaintenance(2) - The device is online, but either the device as a whole, or one or more of its components are in maintenance mode. Maintenance mode could be described as a mode where diagnostics are being run on the device, or some tasks such as device configuration are being excuted on the device that has inhibited its normal operation. vfFrameDisabled(3) - The device has been explicitly disabled from its normal mode of operation, such as when selected as the backup of a redundant pair. vfFrameResetting(4) - The device is in a reset cycle. Any information collected, or dynamic configuration of the device prior to this state may be lost.

vfNumDerivedNotifications.name: vfNumDerivedNotifications
vfNumDerivedNotifications.description: Number of derived notifications defined in vf200 configuration file for this unit. Gives size of derived notifications table.

vfDerivedNotificationTable.name: vfDerivedNotificationTable
vfDerivedNotificationTable.description: Each row contains information about one derived notification defined for the managed VF200 frame.

vfDerivedNotificationEntry.name: vfDerivedNotificationEntry
vfDerivedNotificationEntry.description: A row in the derived notification table.

vfDnFunctionNumber.name: vfDnFunctionNumber
vfDnFunctionNumber.description: Derived Notification Function Number. Identifies derived notification function, define in frame config. file.

vfDnFunctionDescription.name: vfDnFunctionDescription
vfDnFunctionDescription.description: Derived Notification Description. Describes derived notification function for the operator. Set in frame config. file.

vfDnNotificationLevel.name: vfDnNotificationLevel
vfDnNotificationLevel.description: Notification level for this derived notification. selects which trap will be sent for the notification, out of four possible.

vfDnNotificationEnable.name: vfDnNotificationEnable
vfDnNotificationEnable.description: Use to enable or disable this derived notification function.

vfDnNotificationAutoReArm.name: vfDnNotificationAutoReArm
vfDnNotificationAutoReArm.description: Use to enable or disable automatic re-arming of this derived notification function. Auto re-arming allows multiple unacknowledged activations of the derived notification. It re-arms the function after notification so that the specified alarms are again monitored according to the logic function.

vfDnNotificationState.name: vfDnNotificationState
vfDnNotificationState.description: The current state of this derived notification function.

vfDnNotificationAcknowledge.name: vfDnNotificationAcknowledge
vfDnNotificationAcknowledge.description: Use to acknowledge a derived notification. If notificationAutoReArm is disabled, this will re-arm the notification. Otherwise, it is automatically re-armed, and this object is not used.

derivedNotificationLevelA.name: derivedNotificationLevelA
derivedNotificationLevelA.description: A LevelA derived notification was triggered.

derivedNotificationLevelB.name: derivedNotificationLevelB
derivedNotificationLevelB.description: A LevelB derived notification was triggered.

derivedNotificationLevelC.name: derivedNotificationLevelC
derivedNotificationLevelC.description: A LevelC derived notification was triggered.

derivedNotificationLevelD.name: derivedNotificationLevelD
derivedNotificationLevelD.description: A LevelD derived notification was triggered.
